Buy and hold strategy¶

In [8]:
def buy_and_hold(df_price,moment_period,rebalance_period,long_number):
    
    """ This function takes 4 inputs:
        - df_price : DataFrame of stock prices 
        - moment_period : time period of return selected for classifying the long term returns of stocks
        - rebalance_period : time period during which the same classification will apply
        - long_number : optimal number of stocks in which to invest during each rebalance period 
        
        This function returns 3 outputs:
        - df_daily_ret: DataFrame of daily returns
        - df_momentum: DataFrame of returns of a time period of moment_period
        - df_long: DataFrame with values in {0,1}. 0 implies we should not invest in the stock
                    1 implies that we should invest in the stock. Each time period we will select 100
                    firms to invest in based on the results of df_momentum.
        """
    
    ## DataFrame initilization
    
    df_momentum = df_price.pct_change(moment_period).dropna(how='all') # drop lthe first 252 days
    df_daily_ret = df_price.pct_change(1)[df_momentum.index[0]:] # we use the index of df_momentum for all dataframe
    df_price = df_price[df_momentum.index[0]:]
    df_rank = pd.DataFrame(index = df_momentum.index, columns = df_price.columns)
    df_long = pd.DataFrame(index = df_momentum.index, columns = df_price.columns)
    df_long_shifted = pd.DataFrame(index = df_momentum.index, columns = df_price.columns)
    
    
    ## Create DataFrame with ranks of each stock
    
    for i in range(len(df_rank)) : # Modulo technique to compute the rank every 'rebalance_period' 
        if i % rebalance_period == 0 :
            df_rank.iloc[i] = df_momentum.iloc[i].rank(axis=0, ascending=False)
    df_rank = df_rank.ffill() # replace all NAN's with preceding values
                                
    
    ## Create DataFrame with 20 selected stocks
    
    for col in tqdm(df_rank.columns): # 1 = buy, 0 = don't buy ==> long the best stocks
        for i in range(len(df_rank)) :
            if df_rank[col].iloc[i] <= long_number :
                df_long[col].iloc[i] = 1
            else :
                df_long[col].iloc[i] = 0
                
    ### shifting the data, since one cannot invest at the close and know it at the same time
    df_long_shifted = df_long.shift(periods=2, axis=0)
    
    # df_long_shifted is used directly for the buy and hold strategy
    # df_long is only an informative dataframe for the SMA and MACD strategies
    
    return df_daily_ret, df_momentum, df_rank, df_long, df_long_shifted

def long_to_portfolio(df_price,df_daily_ret,df_long) :

    """ 3 inputs:
        - df_price : DataFrame of all stock prices
        - df_daily_ret: DataFrame of all stocks daily returns
        - df: DataFrame of selected stocks with values in {-1,0,1}
        
        1 output:
        - df_port: portfolio value when investing in the stocks of df 
          """
    df_daily_ret = df_daily_ret[df_long.index[0]:]
    df_price = df_price[df_long.index[0]:]
    
    
    # Returns the number of selected stocks at each date. This number is implicitely defined in df
    stocks_number = df_long.iloc[-1].abs().sum() 
    
    df_port = df_daily_ret*df_long
    
    # We add the returns of each line and divide them by the number of selected stocks, thus forming an equal 
    # weighted portfolio. Then, we take the log-return.
    df_port['total_return'] = np.log1p(df_port.sum(axis = 1)/stocks_number)
    df_port['portfolio']= (df_port['total_return']).cumsum()+1
    
    return df_port

def total_return(df_portfolio, port_name ):
    
    ''' Takes 2 inputs:
        - df_portfolio: DataFrame that outputs of the function (long_to_portfolio)
        - port_name: name of the strategy
        
        1 output:
        - Total return in logarithmic scale '''
    
    tot_ret = 100*(df_portfolio.portfolio[-1]-df_portfolio.portfolio[0])/df_portfolio.portfolio[0]
    sharpe = np.sqrt(252)*df_portfolio['total_return'].values.mean()/ df_portfolio['total_return'].values.std()
    print('Total log return of the', port_name,':%.2f' %(tot_ret),'%')
    print('Total Shape Ratio of the', port_name,':%.2f' %(sharpe),'\n')

def SMA_position(df_long,short,long):
    '''This function takes 3 inputs:
    short is the short time horizon of the SMA
    long is the long time horizon of the SMA
    df_long is the DataFrame of selected stocks that contains 1 if the stock is selected and 0 otherwise
    
    This function has 3 outputs:
    df_Position: a dataFrame composed of three values: {-1,0,1}: 1: Sell the stock;
                                                                 0: Don't take any position in the stock
                                                                 1: Buy the stock
    df_sma_short: value of the SMA for the short time horizon
    df_sma_long: value of the SMA for the long time horizon
    '''
    
    # Initialization of DataFrames
    df_Position=pd.DataFrame(index = df_long.index, columns = df_long.columns)
    df_sma_short=pd.DataFrame(index = df_long.index, columns = df_long.columns)
    df_sma_long=pd.DataFrame(index = df_long.index, columns = df_long.columns)

    for tick in tqdm(tickers): 
        df_temp=pd.DataFrame(df_long[tick]).rename(columns={tick: 'Select'})
        df_temp[tick]=df_price[tick]
        
        # We compute the values of SMA for the short and long time period:
        df_sma_short[tick]=talib.SMA(df_price[tick],short)
        df_sma_long[tick]= talib.SMA(df_price[tick],long)
        
        # We compute if SMA_short-SMA_long is positive or negative. If positive we will buy and assign
        # value 1 and if negative we will sell the stock. 
        df_temp['sign']= np.sign( df_sma_short[tick]-df_sma_long[tick])
        
        # This step insures that we buy or sell only if the stock was previously selected (i.e. if df_long=1)
        df_Position[tick]=df_temp['sign']*df_temp['Select']
        
    df_Position=df_Position.shift(periods=2, axis=0).fillna(0)
    return(df_Position, df_sma_short,df_sma_long)

def MACD_position(df_long,fastperiod, slowperiod, signalperiod):
    
    '''This function takes has 4 inputs:
    df_long is the DataFrame of selected stocks that contains 1 if the stock is selected and 0 otherwise
    fastperiod is the medium time horizon of the MACD
    slowperiod is the long time horizon of the MACD
    signalperiod is the short time horizon of the MACD
    
    This function has 3 outputs:
    df_Position: a dataFrame composed of three values: {-1,0,1}: 1: Sell the stock;
                                                                 0: Don't take any position in the stock
                                                                 1: Buy the stock
    df_macd_diff: difference in value of the macd for the short and long term horizons
    df_macd_signal: value of the MACD for the signal period
    '''
    # Initialiation of DataFrames
    df_Position=pd.DataFrame(index = df_long.index, columns = df_long.columns)
    df_macd_diff=pd.DataFrame(index = df_long.index, columns = df_long.columns)
    df_macd_signal=pd.DataFrame(index = df_long.index, columns = df_long.columns)
    
    for tick in tickers: 
        df_temp=pd.DataFrame(df_long[tick]).rename(columns={tick: 'Select'})
        df_temp[tick]=df_price[tick]
        
        #We compute the three necessary curves for the MACD analysis:
        macd_curves=talib.MACD(df_price[tick],fastperiod,slowperiod,signalperiod)
        df_macd_diff[tick]= macd_curves[0] #Difference in value of slowperiod macd and fastperiod macd
        df_macd_signal[tick]= macd_curves[1] # Macd value with signal period
        df_temp['hist']=macd_curves[2] # difference between the two curves aboves: the histogram
        
        # We compute if the histogram is positive or negative. If positive we will buy and assign
        # value 1 and if negative we will sell the stock. 
        df_temp['sign']=np.sign(df_temp['hist'])
        
        # This step insures that we buy or sell only if the stock was previously selected i.e. if df_long=1
        df_Position[tick]=df_temp['sign']*df_temp['Select']
        
    df_Position=df_Position.shift(periods=2, axis=0).fillna(0)
    return(df_Position, df_macd_diff, df_macd_signal)

def first_occurence(ticker):
    '''This function has 1 input: ticker
    
    This function returns two outputs:
    ind1: The first index where the ticker is selected
    ind2: The end of the selecting period
    '''
    
    indices=[]
    temp=df_long_shifted[ticker][np.arange(0,len(df_long_shifted),132)]
    for i in range(len(temp)):
        if temp[i]==1:
            indices.append(i*132)
    ind1=indices[0]
    
    ind2=indices[0]+131
    
    for j in range(len(indices)-1):
        if (indices[j+1]-indices[j])!=132:
            ind2=indices[j]+131
            break
    
    return(ind1,ind2)

def graph(ticker):
    
    '''This function has 1 input: the ticker
        
    This function returns: 3 graphs with buying and selling points for each strategy'''
    
    ind1,ind2=first_occurence(ticker)
    Longs=pd.DataFrame(df_macd[ticker][ind1:ind2]).rename(columns={ticker:'macd'})
    Longs['sma']=df_sma[ticker][ind1:ind2]
    
    Buy_signal=[]
    Sell_signal=[]

    for i in Longs.columns: # For each strategy:
        
        # Obtain a DataFrame containing stock prices if we buy and -stock prices if we sell
        df=pd.DataFrame(Longs[i]) 
        S=df[(df!=df.shift(1))] 
        S=S*(pd.DataFrame(df_price[ticker].loc[S.index]).rename(columns={ticker:i}))
        
        #Obtain two DataFrames according to the sign of S
        Pos=S[S>0]
        Neg=S[S<0]
        
        # Obtain two DataFrames: Buy and Sell, filled with stock prices at the transaction time
        Buy=pd.DataFrame(index=df.index,columns=df.columns)
        Sell=pd.DataFrame(index=df.index,columns=df.columns)
        Buy.loc[Pos.index]=Pos
        Sell.loc[Neg.index]=Neg*-1
        
        
        ax=pd.DataFrame(df_price[ticker][df.index]).plot(figsize=(15,7))
        
        if i=='sma':
            df_temp_sma=pd.DataFrame(df_sma_long[ticker][ind1:ind2]).rename(columns={ticker:'long term sma'})
            df_temp_sma['short term sma']=df_sma_short[ticker][ind1:ind2]
            df_temp_sma.plot(ax=ax)
            
        if i=='macd':
            df_temp_macd=pd.DataFrame(df_macd_diff[ticker][ind1:ind2]).rename(columns={ticker:'long term macd'})
            df_temp_macd['short term macd']=df_macd_signal[ticker][ind1:ind2]
            df_temp_macd.plot(ax=ax)
            
        
        plt.scatter(df.index,Buy, c='green', label='Buy ')
        plt.scatter(df.index,Sell, c='red',label='Sell ')
        plt.title('Buying and selling points for '+i+' strategy')
        plt.ylabel('stock price')
        plt.legend()
        plt.show()
